Spent the last week helping with Maui relief at a local donation hub hosted by @jonesea. A lot of people have been very generous with money, products and their time. I am sure the mainstream media will be moving on to the next big story soon but this tragedy is going to take a very long time to get figured out. So many people lost loved ones along with everything they own. I know life is hard trying to keep a roof over your head but I implore you to help out your fellow humans on Maui. If you have a few bucks throw it their way. If you have product or service you can donate. If you have an afternoon to help one of the donation hubs. Every little bit helps and is appreciated. Thanks for reading.

Happy birthday to my beautiful mom.

Haven’t been too inspired lately. This time of year is hard. I see politicians spending the money of struggling people to bomb innocent families and it disgusts me. It’s my birthday tomorrow. I am feeling old and unlovable. Things just don’t seem to make sense anymore. It’s crazy to see so much beauty in the world tarnished with greed and ego. Hoping this new year brings true peace and happiness to everyone. I am rambling but I was inspired to just doodle this little rat dude this morning. People over profits, power to the people, fuck war. Please try your best to be a decent human. Make more art, hug more loved ones, help folks out and enjoy the ride. Free all oppressed people.
